Procedure: Stent Removal + Y-Stent
Indication: Cancer, blocked stent.
Steps:
1. GA, LMA. Flex scope check.
2. Saw tumor in RMS and blocked stent in LMS.
3. Switched to Rigid Bronch.
4. Used APC and balloon to free up the old stent in LMS. Pulled it out.
5. Cleaned up tumor with APC/Cryo.
6. Measured and cut a new Y-stent.
7. Placed Y-stent. Good position.
Plan: Admit for Rad Onc.
